            <biogHist>
                <p>Mary or Marion was the daughter of Donald Matheson and Ann Matheson n√©e
                    Macaskill, both crofters. She is listed in the 1871 census as a general domestic
                    servant aged 20, working for the family of William Macaulay, a farmer of 200
                    acres, in Trumisgarry, a settlement close to Malacleit where her own family
                    appear to have originated. Ann Matheson died of dropsy in Malacleit in 1879, her
                    son Donald being present. Mary married John MacLeod, a shoemaker from Galder,
                    Glenelg in 1880 in Malacleit, with her brother Donald Matheson as witness.</p>
